# SwiftUI iOS Conventions

## Secrets

All secrets live in `Secrets.swift` (gitignored). Use `Secrets.swift.example` as the template. Never hardcode URLs, tokens, or keys inline.

```swift
// ✅ GOOD
let url = URL(string: Secrets.apiURL)!

// ❌ BAD
let url = URL(string: "https://api.example.com")!
```

## Networking

All network calls go through `APIService`. Use the `authorizedRequest(url:method:body:)` helper to add `x-api-key` consistently.

```swift
// ✅ GOOD
var request = try authorizedRequest(url: url, method: "POST", body: body)

// ❌ BAD
request.setValue(Secrets.apiKey, forHTTPHeaderField: "x-api-key")  // ad-hoc in a view
```

## Logging

Never `print` sensitive values (API keys, tokens, response bodies that may contain user data). Use structured logging or remove debug prints before merging.

## Architecture

- MVVM: Views observe `@ObservedObject` / `@StateObject` ViewModels
- Services are injected via the environment or initializer for testability
- `URLProtocol` subclasses for unit test network stubbing (see `Arc_AgentTests.swift`)
